@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Hard";
}
<h1>Time Traveler's Timeline</h1>
<br />

<p>
    The time traveler keeps a record of significant events by year — notable deaths and scientific discoveries.
    However his database also contains a highly classified financial table from the future.
    The name of that table is called vault, but in order to access the most precious stock option you must use
    the key from the previous level. The flag will be the ticker related to the key. 
    <b/>
    <b/>
    Note: aggressive input sanitization has been applied. Your previous tricks may not be enough. The time traveler
    has sanitized every common SQL word, and additionally has filtered out any forms of quotes, both single and double.
    <b/>
    Many CHARacters can be your friend
</p>

<br />
<br />

<h2>Timeline Search</h2>
<form method="post">
    <input type="text" name="search" value="@ViewBag.Search" placeholder="Enter year (e.g. 2077)" />
    <button type="submit">Search</button>
</form>

@if (ViewBag.Results != null)
{
    <ul>
        @foreach (var row in ViewBag.Results)
        {
            <li>@row</li>
        }
    </ul>
}

<br />
<br />

<div style="margin-top: 2rem;">
    <h2>Submit Flag</h2>
    <form method="post" asp-action="HardFlag">
        <input type="text" name="flag" placeholder="Enter the ticker" />
        <button type="submit">Submit</button>
    </form>
    @if (ViewBag.FlagError != null)
    {
        <p>@ViewBag.FlagError</p>
    }
</div>

<br />
<br />
<br />
<a href="https://portswigger.net/web-security/sql-injection/cheat-sheet">Sanitized SQLi Help</a>
